Project structure:

┌── data
│   ├── raw                   raw data (ready or not ready to analyse)
│   ├── pre                   preprocessed data (ready to analyse)
│   ├── process               processed data
│   ├── interim               data used in intermediate processes
│   └── external              data from external sources
│
├── loteca                    source code root
│   └── data
│       ├── raw               code here will generate data that goes into './data/raw/'
│       ├── pre
│       ├── process
│       └── interim
│
├── notebooks                 jupyter notebooks
│   └── html                  html generated from jupyter notebooks (for reading)
│
└── references                external references (e.g. something about what we are retrieving)


Project reference:

- https://github.com/drivendata/cookiecutter-data-science
- https://towardsdatascience.com/structure-and-automated-workflow-for-a-machine-learning-project-2fa30d661c1e
